class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        long long res = 0;
        int n = s.size();
        for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
            if (s[i] != s[i-1]) {
                res += min(i, n - i);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Observe that any mismatch between adjacent characters must be fixed by flipping either the prefix ending at that position or the suffix starting at that position. The optimal choice is always the cheaper of the two, so we accumulate min(i, n-i) for every transition.

